  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshPro
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Predictable Randomness

    The Netscape SSL Vulnerability (1995)

    Netscape
    generated cryptographic keys using

    predictable values such as the current
    time

    and process identifiers.



    Although the resulting key appeared
    random,

    an attacker could estimate these values and

    reconstruct the
    original seed.



    This reduced the number of possible keys

    from billions
    to only a small set of guesses.



    Lesson:

    A random-looking output is
    not secure if the

    input values are predictable.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
