  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Why Can the Token Be Guessed?


    The generated token appears random.



    However,
    an attacker may know when the

    token was created and can estimate values

    such
    as the process identifiers.



    Instead of testing billions of possibilities,

    the
    attacker only has to test a small number

    of likely inputs.



    Because
    the same inputs always produce the

    same output, the correct token can eventually

    be
    found.'
